Looking at the Qt3Support code, setCurrentText() either finds the existing item in the list and makes it the current selected item, or adds a new item.

So in that case I think this should be:

bookmark_combo_box_->blockSignals(true);

const int index = bookmark_combo_box_->findText( bookmarks_->getName() );

if ( index > -1 ) {
    bookmark_combo_box_->setCurrentIndex( index );
}
else {
    bookmark_combo_box_->addItem( bookmarks_->getName() );
    // Then find the index of new item and     
    bookmark_combo_box_->setCurrentIndex();
}
bookmark_combo_box_->blockSignals(false);

Otherwise you are just changing the item text for the current selected item.

With things like this I'd prefer the original code to be fixed. 

Here we are passing the current layout of the table group box which this layout then gets added to, and then below we then set this layout as the tableGroupBox_'s layout... really nasty. 

It should be just: 
tableLayout_ = new QVBoxLayout( tableGroupBox_ );

and then remove: 
tableGroupBox_->setLayout( tableLayout_ );
